-- Greek-German 10-Year Yield Premium Narrows to Less Than 700 Basis Points
-- B y   P a u l   D o b s o n
-- 2010-10-11T12:58:54Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-11/greek-german-10-year-yield-premium-narrows-to-less-than-700-basis-points.html
The  extra yield  investors demand to
hold Greek 10-year government bonds instead of benchmark German
bunds narrowed to less than 700 basis points for the first time
since June 22.  The difference in yield, or spread, was at 699.9 basis
points as of 1:56 p.m. in London.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Paul Dobson in London at 
 pdobson2@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
